{"questionId":"1244759","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The thermal decomposition of dinitrogen monoxide occurs according to the equation:</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">2N<sub>2</sub>O (g) → 2N<sub>2</sub> (g) + O<sub>2</sub> (g)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The reaction can be followed by measuring the change in total pressure, at constant temperature, with time.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The <em>x</em>-axis and <em>y</em>-axis are shown with arbitrary units.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/bed09cad6f4e06864611862a98d189546b8fbdea.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"564\" height=\"283\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Outline, with a reason, another property that could be monitored to measure the rate of this reaction.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 1</strong></em><br>colour&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong><br>Br2 /reactant is coloured «Br<sup>–</sup> (aq) is not»&nbsp;<strong style=\"color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;white-space:normal;\">[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 2</strong></em><br>conductivity&nbsp;<strong style=\"color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;white-space:normal;\">[✔]</strong><br>greater/increased concentration of ions in products&nbsp;<strong style=\"color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Hel